# 📝 CLI To-Do List Manager - Python

This is a simple command-line **To-Do List** application built using Python as part of the Elevate Labs Python Developer Internship Task 2.

## ✅ Features

- Add tasks to the list
- View all tasks
- Remove completed or unwanted tasks
- Persistent task storage using a text file (`tasks.txt`)

## 🛠️ Technologies Used

- Python 3
- File Handling with `open()`
- Lists and String Manipulation
- Command-line interface (CLI)

## 📂 Files

- `todo.py` – Main script that runs the CLI-based to-do list app
- `tasks.txt` – Text file used to store tasks persistently

